{{Quote|I have to wonder whether the Rebel Alliance command sent you and your squadron here to accomplish anything at all, or whether patrolling Kuat Drive Yards is just a convenient excuse for getting you all safely out of the way, so you won't needlessly interfere with the actual fighters, once the battle begins. I imagine that Mon Mothma has more important things to worry about than how to deploy a so-called squadron that's really little more than laser-cannon fodder.|Kuat of Kuat, to Gennad Rozhdenst|<ref name="Hard Merchandise">''[[Hard Merchandise]]''</ref>}}
'''Scavenger Squadron''' was a [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] that flew for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

A second [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] squadron, made up of [[BTL Y-wing starfighter/Legends|Y-Wings]] and led by [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Gennad Rozhdenst]] was present at [[Kuat/Legends|Kuat]] shortly before and during the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] in an attempt to sway the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] leaders to join the Rebellion and secretly to steal replacement [[Capital ship/Legends|Capital Ships]] after the attack on the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]]. They succeeded in taking four [[Lancer-class frigate/Legends|''Lancer Frigates'']] and an unknown number of [[Zebulon-B frigate|Zebulon-B Frigates]]. At least two members of the squadron [[Death/Legends|died]] when [[Kuat (person)|Kuat of Kuat]] triggered an explosion in an [[Bombing of the Kuat shipyards (4 ABY)|attempt]] to prevent the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] from taking control of the shipyard.

